# Construct Directory Structure

Construct is the standalone editor app (prop/actor/level builder). **Never** add editor logic to `viberanium/` or gameplay logic from `sandbox/`.

## Layout

```
construct/src/
├── ConstructApp.tsx        # package entry re-export only
├── catalog/                # documents, keys, manifest, document↔def converters
│   ├── actors/              # ActorDocument type + parse/serialize/convert
│   ├── props/               # PropDocument type + parse/serialize/convert
│   ├── levels/              # LevelDocument type + parse/serialize/convert + index helpers
│   ├── keys/                # CONSTRUCT_KEYS component key strings
│   ├── manifest/            # KaykitManifest types, loader, tree filters, lookup helpers
│   └── slugify.ts            # shared document-id slugify helper
├── entities/                # factories, components, systems
│   ├── editorCommon/         # shared origin marker, colliders, editableTarget, TRS, materials
│   ├── actorEditor/          # actor root/character/attachment/collider spawn + systems
│   ├── propEditor/           # prop root/part spawn + systems
│   ├── levelEditor/          # level root/origin, prop/actor placements, pivot, picking
│   ├── gizmos/               # move/scale/rotate gizmo meshes, input, picking, system
│   ├── orbit/                # orbit camera + origin marker + anim preview entity
│   ├── viewer/                # standalone preview helpers (model bounds)
│   └── ground/               # spawnGround — editor ground plane
├── scenes/                  # editorScene + installEditorSystems (scene + mode installers)
├── session/                 # preview, propEditor, actorEditor, levelEditor, anim session slices + types
├── globals/                 # bootstrap — thin composition only
├── storage/                 # localStore factory + actor/prop/level local store wrappers
└── ui/
    ├── app/                  # ConstructApp shell + useConstruct* hooks
    ├── explorer/             # AssetExplorer, LevelExplorer, Tree
    ├── inspector/             # Prop/Actor/Level Inspector + Details, shared.tsx, euler
    ├── menu/                  # AppMenu (File menu, mode switch)
    ├── modals/                # Confirm/Load*/Rename/Tag/Group modals
    ├── orientation/           # OrientationCube
    ├── viewer/                # ViewerAnimHud (preview, prop, actor, level)
    └── theme/                 # style.css
```

## Catalog rule

`catalog/` holds document types, parse/serialize, and manifest data — **no registry writes, no spawn logic**.

| Belongs in `catalog/` | Belongs outside `catalog/` |
|-----------------------|----------------------------|
| `PropDocument` / `ActorDocument` / `LevelDocument` types + parse/serialize | `spawnPropEditor`, `spawnActorEditor`, `spawnLevelEditor` |
| `CONSTRUCT_KEYS` component key strings | `install*System` |
| `KaykitManifest` types, `loadKaykitManifest`, tree filters | `bootstrap` composition |
| Document ↔ `PropDefinition`/`ActorDefinition`/`LevelDefinition` converters | Session slices (`session/*`) |
| `slugifyDocumentId` | UI hooks, React components |

**`catalog/` must not import from `entities/`, `session/`, `scenes/`, `globals/`, or `ui/`.**

## Level mode UI (summary)

- Explorer: unified tree with **Simple** (props/actors from manifest), **Standard** (local `.prop`/`.actor`), and **Colliders**; bottom **Import** for `.prop`/`.actor`. `+` places at orbit target.
- Elements: Level → Ground Plane → Player Spawn → Props/Actors (Simple|Standard when non-empty) → Colliders → Groups. Empty subgroups hidden. Ctrl multi-select; group select selects members.
- Details: rename; simple variants; actor `aiPackage`; Group / Delete footer; ground plane and player spawn non-deletable (ground: move+scale only; player spawn: move+yaw only).
- Preview HUD: status + Show colliders (prop/actor/level); Show bones (actor only).
- Gizmos: instance / group root / temp multi-select pivot; world move; TRS relative to level origin; scale collider-only or ground plane; actors/player spawn yaw-only rotate; ground plane no rotate.
- Rotated box colliders (prop parts or level collider placements) serve as **ramps** at runtime — no dedicated ramp type; slope walk/slide behavior is angle-based in the CPU collision resolver.
- Files: `.level` save/load/import/export via `levelLocalStore` (`construct.levelLocalStore`).

## Entity rule

| Folder | Role |
|--------|------|
| `entities/editorCommon/` | Shared mechanics: origin marker, collider shape resources, `editableTarget`, `editorSelection`, materials, TRS, `syncPartLocal` |
| `entities/actorEditor/` | Actor root/character/attachment/collider components + `spawnActor*` + `installActorColliderFollowSystem` |
| `entities/propEditor/` | Prop root/part components + `spawnAssetPart`/`spawnColliderPart`/`spawnPropEditor` |
| `entities/levelEditor/` | Level root/origin, placement spawns, selection pivots, viewport pick helpers |
| `entities/gizmos/` | Move/scale/rotate gizmo meshes, picking, input, `installConstructGizmoSystem` |
| `entities/orbit/` | Orbit camera state, origin marker, anim preview entity, `installConstructOrbitSystem` |

Shared editor mechanics live in `entities/editorCommon/` — never duplicate origin marker, collider, or TRS logic per-editor.

## Session rule

- `session/types.ts` — `ConstructSession`, `ConstructSessionState`, `ConstructSessionDeps` types + `createConstructSessionState`
- `session/preview.ts` — standalone asset preview load/texture-variant slice
- `session/propEditor.ts` — prop document mutation slice
- `session/actorEditor.ts` — actor document mutation slice
- `session/levelEditor.ts` — level document mutation slice (placements, groups, gizmo commit)
- `session/anim.ts` — animation pack load/apply/clear slice

Session slices are pure functions of `(deps, state, ...)` returning updated documents — no React, no JSX. System installers live in `scenes/installEditorSystems.ts`.

## Globals rule

`globals/bootstrap.ts` composes engine primitives into a `ConstructSession` — composition only, no document mutation logic.

## Storage rule

- `storage/localStore.ts` — generic `createLocalStore<TDoc>(storageKey)` factory
- `storage/actorLocalStore.ts` / `storage/propLocalStore.ts` / `storage/levelLocalStore.ts` — thin wrappers

Do not reimplement read/write/list/remove localStorage logic per document type — extend `localStore.ts`.

## UI rule

- `ui/app/ConstructApp.tsx` — layout shell only; delegates to `useConstruct*.ts` hooks
- UI talks only to `ConstructSession` or catalog helpers — **never import `entities/` from `ui/`**
- `ui/inspector/shared.tsx` — shared details helpers

## Forbidden

- Barrel `index.ts` anywhere under `construct/src/`
- Comments in agent-generated `.ts`/`.tsx` source
- God objects in `globals/bootstrap.ts` or `ui/app/ConstructApp.tsx`
- Component key strings outside `catalog/keys/components.ts`
- Duplicated inspector helpers — use `ui/inspector/shared.tsx`
- Duplicated localStorage logic — use `storage/localStore.ts`
- `entities/` imports from `ui/`
- Editing embedded standard prop/actor internals from level mode
